Algorithm (ref) shows the outline for answer inference. We run all relevant documents, {{2209.07250_FO0004||FO}} for a given query though the span prediction model to get the candidate spans comprised of the answer span, {{2209.07250_FO0005||FO}}, and model confidence, {{2209.07250_FO0006||FO}}, (Line 3-4). If the span is non-empty and confidence of the model is higher than a threshold, {{2209.07250_FO0007||FO}}, then we extract integer count from the span using the ExtractCount function (Line 5-6). If the integer extraction in non-empty, we save the span, the extracted integer and the model confidence (Lines 7-9).